# Affordmed - Frontend URL Shortener (Client-only)

## Overview
- React + Material UI app.
- Runs on http://localhost:3000
- All data persisted to browser localStorage.
- Redirection handled via client-side route `/r/:shortcode`.
- Logging integrated: call to test server logging endpoint at http://20.244.56.144/logging-service/logs

## Setup
1. Install dependencies:
   cd frontend-test
   npm install

2. Start the app:
   npm start
   (app will use port 3000)

3. To enable logging:
   - You must register and authenticate with the test server to obtain `access_token`.
   - In `src/api/loggerClient.js` update variable `accessToken` at runtime:
     - Either edit file and set token, OR better, after starting app open browser console and run:
       window.localStorage.setItem('EVAL_ACCESS_TOKEN', '<YOUR_TOKEN>');
       // then refresh
   - Alternatively change code to set token automatically.

## Notes
- Default validity is 30 minutes if left blank.
- Custom shortcode allowed (alphanumeric + _ -), length 3..50. If duplicate, a unique variant is auto-generated.
- All logs are best-effort. Logging failures do not break the app.
